abstract: He’s the “30 Rock” guy in a trucker’s hat. She’s an Olympic hopeful. She gives him lessons, but the instruction flows both ways.
snippet: He’s the “30 Rock” guy in a trucker’s hat. She’s an Olympic hopeful. She gives him lessons, but the instruction flows both ways.
lead_paragraph: In July, as a polite 26-year-old Chinese-born New Yorker named Wu Yue put together a string of table tennis victories at the Pan American Games in Toronto, the cheers from a bearded man wearing a trucker hat were impossible to ignore.

abstract: On the London stage, “Welcome Home, Captain Fox!,” “The Maids” and “The Patriotic Traitor.”
snippet: On the London stage, “Welcome Home, Captain Fox!,” “The Maids” and “The Patriotic Traitor.”
lead_paragraph: LONDON — A telephone suspended in midair provides an aptly Magritte-like opening image for “Welcome Home, Captain Fox!,” a play that tilts reality on its axis so that nothing is quite what it appears. The production, directed by Blanche McIntyre at the Donmar Warehouse through April 16, represents a genuine rarity in a theater capital that prefers to revisit familiar titles.

abstract: A powerful V8 and adaptive suspension give this luxury ride serenity, but the mesmerizing cabin lighting seems to take a cue from the Las Vegas Strip.
snippet: A powerful V8 and adaptive suspension give this luxury ride serenity, but the mesmerizing cabin lighting seems to take a cue from the Las Vegas Strip.
lead_paragraph: A case could be made that modern automobiles are the most impressive consumer products created. Sophisticated cars contain more than 100 million lines of computer code (apparently all of Facebook comes in at about 60 million), and you probably don’t leave your laptop outside in the rain, snow or blistering heat for days on end. If you do, please write and tell me why.

abstract: This was ‘House of Cards’ at its most fast-paced and entertaining.
snippet: This was ‘House of Cards’ at its most fast-paced and entertaining.
lead_paragraph: President Frank Underwood said he wanted an open Democratic National Convention that gave people a show. In this episode, that’s exactly what he and we get: 45 minutes of “House of Cards” at its most fast-paced and entertaining.

abstract: Long before Facebook or Twitter, Mr. Kimsey was a co-founder of AOL, connecting a nascent online audience with news and information as never before.
snippet: Long before Facebook or Twitter, Mr. Kimsey was a co-founder of AOL, connecting a nascent online audience with news and information as never before.
lead_paragraph: Jim Kimsey, a dot-com entrepreneur who helped turn a failed video game company into America Online, the giant dial-up service that helped bring the Internet to the masses, died on Tuesday at his home in McLean, Va. He was 76.

abstract: President Obama’s current standoff with the Senate over replacing Justice Antonin Scalia is a struggle over not just the law, but power and his own legacy.
snippet: President Obama’s current standoff with the Senate over replacing Justice Antonin Scalia is a struggle over not just the law, but power and his own legacy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The first time President Obama sat down to pick a new Supreme Court justice, surprised aides discovered that he had gone beyond the briefing memos to read the leading candidate’s past judicial rulings. The president, a onetime constitutional law teacher, was in his element, a “legal nerd,” as one aide called him, putting theory into practice.
